12. Sabinos: often referred to by Roman authors as a type of simple and virtuous habits, sturdy hardiness, and love of freedom. Ligarius him- self was of Sabine descent. 16. squaloremque: it was a custom among the Romans to show their distress at the death of a relative or friend by studied neglect of appearance.
